pdf_rag_agent/
├── app.py                  # Main Streamlit application
├── requirements.txt
├── .env
├── utils/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── pdf_processor.py    # PDF loading, chunking, embedding
│   ├── agent_builder.py    # Agent, tools, chains
│   ├── extractors.py       # Structured extraction logic
│   └── export_utils.py     # Export to JSON/CSV/Excel
└── data/
    └── (uploaded PDFs)


###dockerfile
docker build -t pdf-rag-agent .
│
├── 1. Pull ubuntu:22.04 base image
│
├── 2. Install system packages (wget, curl, bzip2, ca-certificates)
│
├── 3. Download Miniconda installer (~120MB)
│       └── Install to /opt/conda
│       └── Add conda to PATH
│       └── Clean up installer
│
├── 4. Create conda environment "ragenv" with Python 3.12
│
├── 5. Copy requirements.txt
│       └── pip install all packages inside ragenv
│           ├── streamlit
│           ├── langchain
│           ├── langchain-openai
│           ├── langgraph
│           ├── pypdf
│           ├── pydantic
│           └── ...
│
├── 6. Verify installations (streamlit, langchain, langgraph)
│
├── 7. Copy application code (app.py, utils/, etc.)
│
├── 8. Create Streamlit config (/root/.streamlit/config.toml)
│       └── server.address = 0.0.0.0
│       └── server.port = 8501
│       └── headless = true
│
├── 9. EXPOSE 8501
│
└── 10. Set ENTRYPOINT
        └── conda run -n ragenv streamlit run app.py


docker run -p 8501:8501 --env-file .env --name rag-app pdf-rag-agent
│
├── Container starts
├── Conda activates "ragenv" environment
├── Streamlit server starts on 0.0.0.0:8501
├── Port 8501 forwarded from container → host
│
└── Access at http://localhost:8501
